               \n                    Nicholas Bostick                \n            \n                                    For the past 23 years, the Vans Warped Tour has acted as a training ground for the next generation of mosh pit-prowling punks. With the amalgam of more than 60 bands old and new, heavy and soft, Warped Tour is a one-day touring festival of fun. And this year, veterans like Save Ferris, CKY and Gwar will be in Dallas to give the tour some of its old flair. Originally conceived as an alternative rock show in 1995, the tour quickly became a gathering point for skaters, punks and weirdos after Vans began sponsoring it. The Warped Tour now acts as a sort of catch-all for whats cool with the kids these days while remaining educational by showcasing bands from the late 80s and 90s in their natural habitat: thrashing on stage in front of a screaming mob of kids.
